In other news, here is =E2=80=9CMonetary Tightening and U.S. Bank Fragility=
 in 2023: Mark-to-Market Losses and Uninsured Depositor Runs?=E2=80=9D by=
=C2=A0Erica Xuewei Jiang,=C2=A0Gregor Matvos, Tomasz Piskorski and Amit Ser=
u, dated yesterday:
We analyze U.S. banks=E2=80=99 asset exposure to a recent rise in the inter=
est rates with implications for financial stability. The U.S. banking syste=
m=E2=80=99s market value of assets is $2 trillion lower than suggested by t=
heir book value of assets accounting for loan portfolios held to maturity. =
Marked-to-market bank assets have declined by an average of 10% across all =
the banks, with the bottom 5th percentile experiencing a decline of 20%. We=
