10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Bailouts etc.</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t think that anything interestin=
g turns on whether or not this weekend=E2=80=99s resolution of=C2=A0Silicon=
 Valley Bank was a =E2=80=9Cbailout,=E2=80=9D so let=E2=80=99s not discuss =
that.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: =
transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But when people talk about bank bailouts, what they often mean to=
 talk about is moral hazard, the idea that if the government saves=C2=A0peo=
ple from the consequences of bad bank behavior, that will encourage more ba=
d bank behavior in the future. And that seems worth talking about.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is, I think, fair to say that Silicon Valle=
y Bank took some bad risks, and that=E2=80=99s why it ended up failing. It =
is a bit harder to say exactly <em>what</em> SVB=E2=80=99s bad decision was=
. A simple answer is =E2=80=9Cit made a huge bet on interest rates staying =
low, which most prudent banks would not have done, and it blew up.=E2=80=9D=
 Yesterday <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3083546=
3.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMT=
Mvc3ZiLWZhaWx1cmUtc3BhcmtzLWJsYW1lLWdhbWUtb3Zlci10cnVtcC1lcmEtcmVndWxhdG9ye=
S1yb2xsYmFjaz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzE0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0=
bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMTQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R=
1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe8dd5b95" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Bloomberg reported that</=
a> =E2=80=9Cin late 2020, the firm=E2=80=99s asset-liability committee rece=
ived an internal recommendation to buy shorter-term bonds as more deposits =
flowed in,=E2=80=9D to reduce its duration risk, but that would have reduce=
d earnings, and so =E2=80=9Cexecutives balked=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccontinu=
ed to plow cash into higher-yielding assets.=E2=80=9D They took imprudent d=
uration risk, ignored objections,=C2=A0and it blew them up.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think that answer is fine. A <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhh=
ZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl=
1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzE0JnV0bV9jYW1wYW=
lnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa05d04ec" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  more compli=
cated answer</a> would be that they took duration risk, as banks generally =
do, but their real sin was having a concentrated set of=C2=A0<em>depositors=
=C2=A0</em>who were uninsured, quick-moving, well-informed, herd-like and v=
ery rates-sensitive in their own businesses: If all of your money is demand=
 deposits from tech startups who will withdraw it at the slightest sign of =
trouble and/or higher rates, you should not be investing it in long-term bo=
nds. This is a more subtle answer than =E2=80=9Cjust hedge your rate risk b=
ro,=E2=80=9D and it is arguably more=C2=A0<em>understandable=C2=A0</em>that=
 SVB=E2=80=99s executives would get it wrong,<a class=3D"footnote-index" hr=
ef=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: in=
line-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0but in any case it certainly ended up being a bad risk.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So if SVB was=C2=A0<em>rewarded=C2=A0</em>for =
taking these risks that blew it up, that would be bad; that would be =E2=80=
=9Cmoral hazard.=E2=80=9D But the way the Silicon Valley Bank resolution wo=
rked is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">SVB was seized by the Federal Deposit=
 Insurance Corp. on Friday, and by Sunday night the FDIC and other regulato=
rs announced that all of SVB=E2=80=99s depositors =E2=80=94=C2=A0including =
those who were above the FDIC=E2=80=99s usual $250,000 insurance limit =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0would be able to get all of their money back on Monday. So the =
depositors were fully rescued.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The=
 shareholders, bondholders and executives were not: The executives were rem=
oved; the shares, which closed at $267.83 last Wednesday, are almost certai=
nly worth zero<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>; the bonds are also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjMtMDMtMTMvc3ZiLWJvbmRzLXRoZS11cy1zYXlzLXdpbGwtYmUtd2lwZWQtb3V0LWdhaW4=
taW4tcmFyZS1zZXNzaW9uP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMTQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW=
1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249b=
W9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe0e6dd7a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  probably impaire=
d</a>=C2=A0and possibly a zero.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What lessons will rational actors take from th=
is? I mean:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a depositor =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
in particular, a business that needs more than $250,000 of cash to operate =
efficiently =E2=80=94=C2=A0you should be much less concerned about risk-tak=
ing by your bank, because if your bank fails the government will probably r=
escue you.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a bank execu=
tive or shareholder or probably bondholder, you should be=C2=A0<em>more=C2=
=A0</em>concerned about risk-taking by your bank, because you have seen tha=
t it can lead to executives and shareholders and bondholders getting zeroed=
, and that the government won=E2=80=99t rescue you if that happens.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so the question is: Is that moral hazard? =
Well, not for shareholders and executives and bondholders. I suppose it is =
moral hazard for depositors, and a resolution of SVB that left depositors w=
ith losses would force depositors to pay closer attention to the risks thei=
r banks are taking. (Cliff Asness <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9jbGlmZm9yZGFzbmV=
zcy9zdGF0dXMvMTYzNTExNzkyNzUxODMxMDQwNA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf2fdce92" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;"> on Twitter</a>: =E2=80=9CThe moral hazard here is we=E2=80=99ve gr=
eatly reduced the incentive for depositors of any size now =E2=80=A6 to act=
ually give a moment=E2=80=99s thought to the riskiness of where they=E2=80=
=99re putting their money.=E2=80=9D)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I think the modern bank-regulatory view is=
=C2=A0that=C2=A0<em>the point of a bank deposit is that you shouldn=E2=80=
=99t have to worry about it</em>, and that it is a=C2=A0<em>failure=C2=A0</=
em>of bank regulation if depositors of any size have =E2=80=9Cto actually g=
ive a moment=E2=80=99s thought to the riskiness=E2=80=9D of a bank. (Bank d=
eposits are meant to be =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmJlci5vcmcvcGFwZXJzL3cyNjA3=
NA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcc168de1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">information insensitive</a>.=
=E2=80=9D)=C2=A0There are vast areas of life where we don=E2=80=99t worry a=
bout moral hazard. We don=E2=80=99t say things like =E2=80=9Cthe moral haza=
rd of food safety regulation is that we=E2=80=99ve greatly reduced the ince=
ntive for consumers to give a moment=E2=80=99s thought to the riskiness of =
their supermarket=E2=80=99s supply chain.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s not a thi=
ng you=E2=80=99re supposed to think about!=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly the riskiness of a bank=E2=80=99s as=
set/liability mix is absolutely a thing that lots of people =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
bank executives, bank directors, bank regulators, bank shareholders, bank d=
erivatives counterparties =E2=80=94=C2=A0are supposed to think about.<a cla=
ss=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent=
 !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
