f4b8524a319a23cBb0d46737" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">down big toda=
y</a>, though presumably they=E2=80=99d be down=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>wit=
hout these measures.) The rescue of Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=99s depositor=
s comes too late for Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=99s shareholders, but it=E2=
=80=99s good for every similar bank=E2=80=99s shareholders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a matter of rough justice you could imagine=
 the Fed looking at the=C2=A0<em>most=C2=A0</em>similar bank =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0arguably Signature, with its huge proportion of uninsured deposits and i=
ts exposure to fast-money crypto/tech customers =E2=80=94=C2=A0and saying =
=E2=80=9Cno, not you,=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>shareholders are getting toas=
ted.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way for bank regulators to reduce the mora=
l-hazard impact of the SVB rescue is to take some <em>other</em> banks=E2=
=80=99 shareholders out and shoot them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is that what happened?=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t kn=
ow! It=E2=80=99s possible that Signature was shut due to a traditional bank=
 run. Reyes reports that =E2=80=9CSignature lost 20% of its deposits on Fri=
day=E2=80=9D; Signature (and its board member Barney Frank) said that its o=
utflows had stabilized and that it had enough cash, but the New York Depart=
ment of Financial Services apparently disputes=C2=A0that. But DFS leads wit=
h =E2=80=9Ca significant crisis of confidence in the bank=E2=80=99s leaders=
hip.=E2=80=9D If you are a bank regulator and you think that a bank is (1) =
poorly managed and taking bad risks but also (2) not going to disappear bec=
ause you went and guaranteed all the deposits,=C2=A0<em>you can make it dis=
appear anyway</em>, and arguably you should.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One other point on this subject. If you are a =
banking regulator and you think that the regional banks have taken too much=
 risk and are now undercapitalized given their unrealized losses on=C2=A0he=
ld-to-maturity securities, then the=C2=A0<em>most</em> obvious next thing t=
o do =E2=80=94=C2=A0after the weekend=E2=80=99s actions of promising to fin=
ance those securities at par, but before rewriting any regulations =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0is to make those banks raise capital to fix their balance sheets. =
This is good simply as a matter of sound banking: You don=E2=80=99t want yo=
ur banks to be undercapitalized, so if they are =E2=80=94=C2=A0on whatever =
accounting measure you prefer =E2=80=94=C2=A0then they should get more capi=
tal. It is also good as a matter of punishing shareholders to avoid moral h=
azard: Bank stocks have been absolutely wrecked, and making banks raise mor=
e equity now at these prices will be a painful dilution for existing shareh=
olders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, it=E2=80=99s tricky: Silico=
n Valley Bank did (more or less) the responsible thing last week by trying =
to raise equity to shore up its balance sheet, and=C2=A0<em>that=E2=80=99s =
what brought it down</em>, as people <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvN2U3=
ZmRkZGItNzI0Yy00MmZkLTk4ZWUtNWQ3MjQ4ZDUzMzM0P3JlZj10aGUtZGlmZg/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBa5909cc8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> saw the equity raise and panicked</a>. I do=
ubt anyone wants to be the=C2=A0<em>next=C2=A0</em>regional bank to go out =
with a marketed stock offering. And a bank regulatory climate that is too p=
unitive for shareholders will make it hard for banks to sell more stock, wh=
ich is the main thing they should be doing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess that is the tension now. Bank regulato=
rs want depositors to feel like they are not taking a risk by keeping their=
 money in the bank. They want the banks and their shareholders not to take =
risks with those depositors=E2=80=99=C2=A0money. But they do still want sha=
reholders to take the risk of owning bank stock.=C2=A0</p>
