=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The complaint states that quarterly and annual=
 financial reports from the bank did not take into account warnings that th=
e Federal Reserve gave about raising interest rates.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure. Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdG9yYWdlLmNvdXJ=
0bGlzdGVuZXIuY29tL3JlY2FwL2dvdi51c2NvdXJ0cy5jYW5kLjQwOTQyNy9nb3YudXNjb3VydH=
MuY2FuZC40MDk0MjcuMS4wLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBef6c2827" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> th=
e complaint</a>. SVB=E2=80=99s annual reports =E2=80=9Cunderstated the risk=
s posed to the Company by not disclosing that likely interest rate hikes, a=
s outlined by the Fed, had the potential to cause irrevocable damage to the=
 Company,=E2=80=9D sure. I don=E2=80=99t know how much money they=E2=80=99l=
l get out of the holding company at this point, but I do think that as a se=
curities class action lawyer you are just sort of professionally obligated =
to file this suit so here it is.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/30835463.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9qdXN0aWNl=
LWRlcGFydG1lbnQtc2VjLWludmVzdGlnYXRpbmctc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktYmFua3MtY29sbGF=
wc2UtYzE5MmMyYjI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaffbfadc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Elsewhere</a>:<=
/p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Justice Department and the Securities and =
Exchange Commission are investigating the collapse of Silicon Valley Bank, =
according to people familiar with the matter, after the California lender w=
as taken over by regulators last week amid a historic run on its deposits.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The separate probes are in their preliminary p=
hases and may not lead to charges or allegations of wrongdoing. Prosecutors=
 and regulators often open investigations after financial institutions or p=
ublic companies suffer big, unexpected losses. Shares in SVB Financial Grou=
p, which formerly owned the bank, fell 60% last week and have been stopped =
from trading since Friday.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The investigations are also examining stock sa=
les that SVB Financial=E2=80=99s officers made days before the bank failed,=
 the people said.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I said above that, as a moral hazard matter, S=
VB=E2=80=99s executives are out of their jobs and their shares are zeroed, =
which is a good warning to other risk-loving bank executives. But several o=
f them sold stock just before the failure, so they are not=C2=A0<em>really=
=C2=A0</em>zeroed, and you can see how that would rub people the wrong way.=
 My own impression is that this is<em>=C2=A0</em>unlikely to be insider tra=
ding: SVB=E2=80=99s balance-sheet problems were disclosed and known weeks a=
go, and I gather that SVB=E2=80=99s executives were as surprised as anyone =
else by the run last week. But, still, it doesn=E2=80=99t look great.</p>
